Interactive Architecture is a sound and visual installation made for the Cezanne 2025 exhibition in Aix-en-Provence (France), driven by Hexalab.

It's consist of a visual part running on TouchDesigner for the 360° screen, a sound part running on VCVRack and a physical interface for four people to control sound and visual.
In each of the four 'sit' of the instrument, there is one iR sensor and three potentiometer, modulating a VCVRack and a TouchDesigner part.
An audio transducer is placed below the instrument, vibrating itself by the soundfrequency.
Some sand is on the instrument, revealing sound shape on it by the vibrations.

